extends base
block content
  .faq
    .intro
    h2 Welcome to Uruguay
    .container
      .row
        .col-md-12
          p
            | We know getting to a new country can be difficult some times. This is an attempt to make this easier but if you still have doubts please send us an email to 
            a(href='mailto:hola@jsconf.uy') hola@jsconf.uy
            |.
      h2 Getting to Montevideo
      .row
        .col-md-4          
          h4 By Plane:
          br
          p
            | The 
            a(href='http://www.aeropuertodecarrasco.com.uy/en/') Carrasco Internation Airpot 
            | (IATA: MVD) is located 15km from the city and all major airlines operate.
          p
            | Once you arrive you can choose to take a taxy (UYU 1500) a remise (UYU 800) or a bus (UYU 31) to the city.
      
        .col-md-4
          h4 By Boat:
          br
          p
            | Boats are operated from Montevideo to Buenos Aires and viceversa by  
            a(href='http://www.buquebus.com.uy/') Buquebus 
            |. There are several boats a day and the trip usually takes 3 hours.
        
        .col-md-4
          h4 By Bus:
          br
          p
            | Several companies operates bus travels to Montevideo. Ferry companies also have trips from Buenos Aires to 
            a(href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colonia_del_Sacramento') Colonia 
            | and continue from there to Montevideo by bus.
          p
            | All international buses arrive to 
            a(href='http://www.trescruces.com.uy/') Tres Cruces 
            | the main city terminal.
      h2 Lodging & Accomodation
      .row
        .col-md-12
          p.text-center
            | We have set up a 
            a(href='/hotels') special section of the site 
            | listing a lot of hotels and other resources.
      h2 Useful Information
      .row
        .col-md-6
          ul
            li 
              | Exchange rate is ~21. You can check the daily rate at 
              a(href='http://www.bcu.gub.uy/Paginas/Default.aspx') Banco Central del Uruguay 
              | (National Bank).
            li 
              | No need to go to a bank to change money. 
              | There are exchange houses all over the city and most merchants will accept dollars at a fair rate.
            li 
              | Electricity is 220v and the regular electric outlet is 3 in line.
        .col-md-6
          ul
            li 
              a(href='http://www.lonelyplanet.com/uruguay') Uruguay in Lonley Planet Guide
            li 
              a(href='http://www.uruguaynatural.tv/english') Uruguay in videos (English subs)
          